      "content": "I get that socio-economic stuff is a huge factor, but some researchers argue that even when you control for those variables, there's still a gap that shows up in the data. Can you list some of the specific studies or names of researchers who argue that there are biological or genetic components to these differences? I want to see the arguments that support the more controversial side of the debate for my project.",
